***************************** T A L Y S **************************5728 1451
                                                                  5728 1451
TALYS is a computer code system for the prediction and analysis   5728 1451
of nuclear reactions. TALYS simulates reactions that involve      5728 1451
neutrons, gamma-rays, protons, deuterons, tritons, helions and    5728 1451
alpha-particles, in the 1 keV - 200 MeV energy range. This is     5728 1451
achieved by implementing a suite of nuclear reaction models into  5728 1451
a single code system. This nuclear data file is based on a        5728 1451
theoretical analysis that utilizes the optical model, compound    5728 1451
nucleus statistical theory, fission, direct reactions and         5728 1451
pre-equilibrium processes, in combination with databases and      5728 1451
models for nuclear structure. The following output of TALYS is    5728 1451
stored in this data file:                                         5728 1451
                                                                  5728 1451
- Total, elastic and non-elastic cross sections                   5728 1451
- Inelastic cross sections to discrete states                     5728 1451
- Exclusive channel cross sections, e.g. (n,g), (n,2n), (n,np),.. 5728 1451
- Inelastic scattering angular distributions to discrete states   5728 1451
- Exclusive channel energy spectra                                5728 1451
- Exclusive channel double-differential spectra                   5728 1451
- Exclusive gamma production for discrete states and continuum    5728 1451
- Elastic scattering angular distributions                        5728 1451
- Recoil data                                                     5728 1451
- Total particle cross sections, e.g. (n,xn), (n,xp),..           5728 1451
- Total particle energy spectra                                   5728 1451
- Total particle double-differential spectra                      5728 1451
- Isomeric and ground state cross sections                        5728 1451
- Residual production cross sections                              5728 1451
                                                                  5728 1451
For a description of the used nuclear models and their            5728 1451
parameterization we refer to [kon12]. If for this specific        5728 1451
nuclide we deviate from the global parameterization, it is made   5728 1451
explicit above under Nuclide Specific Information.                5728 1451
