##### MF33: COVARIANCES OF NEUTRON CROSS SECTIONS                 5728 1451
                                                                  5728 1451
In MF33, we store the covariances of most, but not all, reaction  5728 1451
channels that are given in MF3. All covariances are generated     5728 1451
with the TASMAN code [kon12], which generates TALYS runs using    5728 1451
a Monte Carlo parameter method.                                   5728 1451
For each MT-number, the information consists of:                  5728 1451
1. Covariances for MTa, Ea and MTa, Ea (variances)                5728 1451
2. Covariances for MTa, Ea and MTa, Eb (correlations for the      5728 1451
   same reaction channel between different energies)              5728 1451
3. Covariances for MTa, Ea and MTb, Ea (correlations between      5728 1451
   different reaction channels for the same energy)               5728 1451
4. Covariances for MTa, Ea and MTb, Eb (correlations between      5728 1451
   different reaction channels for different energies)            5728 1451
Classes 1 and 2 are covered by NI-type subsubsections with        5728 1451
flag LB=5, followed by a LB=8 section which contains              5728 1451
the cross section variances multiplied by 1.e-3. Next, classes 3  5728 1451
and 4 are covered by flag LB=6 to account for the different       5728 1451
energy grids that two correlating MT-sections may have. Since     5728 1451
the total correlation matrix is fully symmetric, we only need to  5728 1451
include the correlation elements between different MT-numbers     5728 1451
once, and we do that in the subsection with the lowest of the     5728 1451
two MT-numbers. We include covariance information for all the     5728 1451
total cross sections, the lumped partial cross sections and the   5728 1451
individual inelastic cross sections per level (MT51,...). We do   5728 1451
not include covariances for MT600 and higher MT-numbers. For the  5728 1451
most important channels, we include cross-channel correlations.   5728 1451
                                                                  5728 1451
##### MF34: COVARIANCES OF ANGULAR DISTRIBUTIONS                  5728 1451
                                                                  5728 1451
In MF34, we store the covariances of the elastic scattering       5728 1451
angular distributions that are given in MF4/MT2. All covariances  5728 1451
are generated with the TASMAN code [kon12], which generates       5728 1451
TALYS runs using a Monte Carlo parameter method. The tables are   5728 1451
